{
  "stem": "935.9",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And somehow, I managed to get into this group of the 700 women who were supposed to be brought out by Count Bernadotte and managed to get my friend Eva, a Czech, also through by putting a scarf around her and teaching her the Dutch pronunciation of where we lived in Amsterdam, and told her not to open her mouth, because there was one less who could go from the Belgian and Dutch people.",
      "word_count": 74
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were supposed to come for us, and they didn't come.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were brought up to a little camp I didn't even know was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "A man's camp above, perhaps 1/2 a mile from our camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was already completely empty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They already had gone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't know, evacuated, freed, whatever.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And there only were a couple of Czech guys, because there were sick people there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Shortly before I got my [INAUDIBLE] for the very first time, American Red Cross packages were allowed in the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And that is when I was officially declared non-Jewish, which means I didn't get a package, either.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "No package.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "No Red Cross package.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And up there in that camp, there were a few sick people, because they had gotten packages, and unfortunately opened it and ate butter like this and chocolate like this.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And got of course, dysentery and very sick.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So these two Czech guys was there to guard them, invited Eva and me for the first night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They had stolen a lot of, I don't know, whiskey or some drinks which they had grabbed from the Germans who had fled.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "For a drink.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "That very first night, while we were there, Eva was drunk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I drank that thing, it didn't do anything to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "It was like water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I have no idea why.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
